The Herald Conrad Mupesa Mashonaland West Bureau ZANU-PF First Secretary President Emmerson Mnangagwa has arrived in Chegutu for the national clean-up campaign and the party’s star rally today. <img class="size-full wp-image-604400" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.34.33-AM.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.34.33-AM.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.34.33-AM-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Mr Pardon Mukudu, provincial forestry commission head explains to President Mnangagwa the benefits of Kigelia Africana Sausage Tree (Mvee) that he is expected to plant. He is expected to plant a tree at the town’s Community Development Centre in Ward 9. <img class="size-full wp-image-604396 aligncenter" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.33.17-AM.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.33.17-AM.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-04-at-10.33.17-AM-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />
Several Cabinet Ministers and senior party officials are in attendance.